ing patterns in mtDNA and nuclear markers are often due to differences in dispersal, and here it could be both as a result of isolation in refugia during the last glacial maximum and female philopatry and male-biased dispersal. In conclusion, this study shows the importance of both the nuclear and mitochondrial DNA in resolving phylogen\u00ad etic relationships and species histories.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Laine, Veronika N", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "S\u00e4vilammi, Tiina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wahlberg, Niklas", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Meramo, Katarina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ossa, Gonzalo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Johnson, Joseph S", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Blomberg, Anna S", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Yeszhanov, Aidyn B", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Yung, Veronica", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Paterson, Steve", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lilley, Thomas M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Huchon, Doroth\u00e9e", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/a3e51e386507d6793593d0bff1b9eec5", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/dd4d7cc051cf783bb60ef2546769fc69eeff931ac60fcfe825caf62088a19113", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/7M7QA2KY", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/7M7QA2KY", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/36ed63d0a83d1eeeab5a2afdce70fc3d!/b177157-179712", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "schem